In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. recognizes and celebrates Asian American and Native Hawaiian/Pacific Islander Heritage Month. He highlights the history and achievements of Asian Americans, Native Hawaiians, and Pacific Islanders, emphasizing their diverse contributions to American culture and society. The President acknowledges the challenges faced by AANHPI communities, including systemic barriers to economic justice, health equity, educational attainment, and personal safety. He also addresses the increased fear and acts of violence experienced by Asian American communities during the COVID-19 pandemic, condemning these acts and affirming his administration's commitment to standing with AANHPI communities. President Biden acknowledges the historical injustices and discrimination faced by AANHPI communities and calls for federal leadership to promote inclusion and acceptance. He urges all Americans to learn more about the history and cultures of Asian Americans, Native Hawaiians, and Pacific Islanders and to observe the month with appropriate programs and activities.